        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  HIV-infected adults (â‰¥18-70 years of age)

          -  Documented positive HIV-1 ELISA;

          -  On ART for a minimum of 6 months (NOTE: If on ART for 6-12 months, then subjects need
             to have a plasma viral load value < 400 copies/mL at 6 months, and if on ART for > 12
             months, then enrolled participants need to have a minimum of 2 fully suppressed plasma
             viral load values (i.e. < 400 copies/mL) on their most recent viral load blood draws);

          -  Average (based on aim 1 screening) uACR between 30-300 mg/g;

          -  eGFR >30 ml/min/1.73m2 (based on aim 1 screening using CKD-EPI-Cr-CyC equation);

          -  Not currently receiving an ACEi and/or ARB ; and

          -  If female, non-pregnant (documentation of negative urine pregnancy test or current use
             of modern contraceptive method).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Age > 70 years

          -  eGFR of <30 ml/min/1.73m2 (CKD-EPI-Cr-CyC);

          -  uACR > 300 mg/g (as this represents sub-nephrotic albuminuria, and most would agree
             that treatment with an ACEi/ARB is clinically indicated);

          -  Potassium >5.0 meEq/L or reasons to be concerned about hyperkalemia;

          -  Diabetes mellitus (defined by a random glucose > 200 mg/dL or fasting glucose >140
             mg/dL), as all diabetics would qualify for treatment with an ACEi or ARB;

          -  Poorly controlled hypertension (specifically, three or more blood pressure readings
             >160/110 over the past 3 months);

          -  Congestive heart failure (chronic);

          -  Relative hypotension (BP <90/60);

          -  Pregnancy; or

          -  Lack of suitability as a study candidate (consistent alcohol, drug, and/or traditional
             medication use, and/or history of poor compliance).
